Johannesburg – The presidency of South Africa has confirmed that President Cyril Ramaphosa will address the nation tonight at 8 pm on government’s latest response to the coronavirus pandemic. The President’s address will follow meetings of the National Coronavirus Command Council, the President’s Coordinating Council and Cabinet which took place during the course of the day, the presidency said. “As South Africa rolls out its COVID–19 vaccination programme, government and social partners are continuously monitoring infection, treatment and patient recovery rates as well as compliance with health regulations and other prevention measures,” the presidency said in a statement. Watch live: Cyril Ramaphosa addresses nation on third wave The President’s address will be broadcast and streamed on a range of platforms that are accessible to South Africans and international audiences. The latest data from the country’s Department of Health indicated that 21 610 new Covid-19 cases were recorded with 265 more deaths.  Also read: Nomcebo drags record label to court for unpaid royalties for Jerusalema Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here. Sunday World Ashley Lechman